@page "/privacy"

<div class="legal-page">
	<h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
	<p><strong>Last updated:</strong> August 29, 2025</p>
	<p>Taxi Boat Baltic (“we”, “our services”) values your privacy and is committed to protecting your personal data. This Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use, and safeguard your information.</p>

	<h2>1. Information We Collect</h2>
	<p>When you use our services, we may collect the following data:</p>
	<ul>
		<li>
			<strong>Personal information</strong>: name, email, phone number (when making a booking).
		</li>
		<ili>
			<strong>Payment information</strong>: processed securely via <strong>Stripe</strong>. We do not store your card details.
		</ili>
		<li>
			<strong>Usage data</strong>: basic information about your interaction with our website (cookies, device type, browser).
		</li>
	</ul>

	<h2>2. How We Use Your Information</h2>
	<p>We use your data for:</p>
	<ul>
		<li>Managing bookings and providing services.</li>
		<li>Communicating with you (confirmation, reminders, customer support).</li>
		<li>Processing payments securely via Stripe.</li>
		<li>Meeting legal and regulatory requirements. </li>
	</ul>
	<p>We do not sell or rent your personal data to third parties.</p>

	<h2>3. Payments</h2>
	<p>All payments are handled securely by <strong>Stripe</strong>.</p>
	<p>Stripe processes your card information in compliance with PCI-DSS security standards.</p>
	<p>We never store or have access to your full payment details.</p>

	<h2>4. Cookies</h2>
	<p>Our website uses cookies to improve user experience.</p>
	<ul>
		<li>
			<strong>Essential cookies</strong>: required for site functionality.
		</li>
		<li>
			<strong>Analytical cookise</strong> (if used, e.g., Google Analytics): help us understand site traffic.
		</li>
	</ul>
	<p>You can manage cookies through your browser settings.</p>

	<h2>5. Data Retention</h2>
	<p>We keep your booking data only as long as necessary to provide the service and comply with legal obligations.</p>
	<p>Invoices and payment records are stored according to Croatian/EU tax regulations.</p>

	<h2>6. Your Rights (GDPR)</h2>
	<p>Under EU law (GDPR), you have the right to:</p>
	<ul>
		<li>Access your personal data. </li>
		<li>Request correction or deletion.</li>
		<li>Restrict or object to processing.</li>
		<li>Request transfer of your data.</li>
		<li>Withdraw consent (where applicable).</li>
	</ul>
	<p>You can exercise these rights by contacting us.</p>

	<h2>7. Data Security</h2>
	<p>We implement technical and organizational measures to protect your data against unauthorized access, alteration, disclosure, or destruction.</p>
	<p>However, no internet transmission is 100% secure, and we cannot guarantee absolute security.</p>

	<h2>8. Third-Party Services</h2>
	<p>We may use third-party services for:</p>
	<ul>
		<li>Payment processing (Stripe).</li>
		<li>Map services (Google Maps, Leaflet).</li>
	</ul>

	<h2>9. Contact</h2>
	<p>If you have any questions about this Privacy Policy or your data rights, contact us:</p>
